FDis

# Load shapley values
load("./data/rdata_files/shapley_values_fdis_999.RData")
shapley_values_fdis <- shapley_values

VARImp

autoplot(shapley_values_fdis) +
          theme_bw() +
          theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 20),
               axis.title = element_text(size = 20, face = "bold"),
               axis.title.x = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25),
               axis.title.y = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25))

autoplot(shapley_values_fdis, type = "contribution", num_features = 13) +
          theme_bw() +
          theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 20),
               axis.title = element_text(size = 20, face = "bold"),
               axis.title.x = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25),
               axis.title.y = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25))

Explain

shap_long_fdis <-
     as.data.frame(shapley_values_fdis) %>%
          tibble::rownames_to_column("plot") %>%
          pivot_longer(!plot,
                         names_to = "variable",
                         values_to = "shap_value")
ggplot(data = shap_long_fdis, aes(x = variable, y = shap_value, color = shap_value)) +
          geom_point() +
          viridis::scale_colour_viridis("Shapley\nValue",option = "inferno") +
          coord_flip() +
          theme_minimal() +
          geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed",
                color = "#9d9d9d", linewidth = 1) +
          ylab("SHAP value (impact on model output)") +
          xlab("") +
          theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 20),
               axis.title = element_text(size = 20, face = "bold"),
               axis.title.x = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25),
               axis.title.y = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25)) +
          geom_jitter(aes(colour = shap_value), width = 0.2)

shapley_fdis_prec <- ggplot(data = shapley_values_fdis,
          aes(x = predictors$prec, y = shapley_values_fdis$prec)) +
          geom_point() +
          theme_bw() +
          geom_smooth(span = 5) +
          ylab("Shapley Value FDis") +
          xlab("Precipitation") +

shap_redundancy_prec <- ggplot(data = shapley_values_redundancy,
          aes(x = predictors$prec, y = shapley_values_redundancy$prec)) +
          geom_point() +
          theme_bw() +
          geom_smooth(span = 0.6) +
          ylab("Shapley Value Redundancy") +
          xlab("Precipitation") +
          theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 20),
               axis.title = element_text(size = 20, face = "bold"),
               axis.title.x = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25),
               axis.title.y = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25))
shap_redundancy_elev  <- ggplot(data = shapley_values_redundancy,
          aes(x = predictors$elev, y = shapley_values_redundancy$elev)) +
          geom_point() +
          theme_bw() +
          geom_smooth(span = 0.6) +
          ylab("Shapley Value Redundancy") +
          xlab("Elevation") +
          theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 20),
               axis.title = element_text(size = 20, face = "bold"),
               axis.title.x = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25),
               axis.title.y = element_text(color = "grey20", size = 25))
shap_redundancy_acidity  <- ggplot(data = shapley_values_redundancy,

          theme_bw() +

         theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 20),
